# MCP SOTA Standards (Centralized)

This repository follows the Model Context Protocol (MCP) SOTA standards managed in the `mcp-central-docs` repository.

## Core References
- [STANDARDS.md](file:///d:/Dev/repos/mcp-central-docs/STANDARDS.md)
- [gemini.md](file:///d:/Dev/repos/mcp-central-docs/gemini.md)
- [cursor.md](file:///d:/Dev/repos/mcp-central-docs/docs/ecosystem/cursor/README.md)

## Key Requirements
1. **Config & Log Locations**: Refer to Section 2.3 in [STANDARDS.md](file:///d:/Dev/repos/mcp-central-docs/STANDARDS.md) for standardized Windows paths.
2. **Startup Diagnostics**: Section 2.3 contains crucial paths for debugging startup failures (e.g., `%APPDATA%\Claude\logs` or `%APPDATA%\Cursor\logs`).
3. **FastMCP Compliance**: Use FastMCP 2.14.1+ standards for tool families, portmanteau patterns, and structured returns.

When implementing new tools or modifying server logic, always ensure compliance with the centralized standards to maintain the "neural grid" alignment.
